description: A TPSR is a connection protocol file used by the TeamViewer Assist AR (previously known as TeamViewer Pilot). Information stored in a TPSR file is stored in compressed ZIP file format. TPSR contains detailed history of TeamViewer connection between an expert and a technician for resolving issue and reviewal purpose. Information contained inside a TPSR file includes device type, name, Assist AR ID, Expert ID, date and time, and duration of the connection. This data is stored in a JSON file inside the compressed TPSR archive.

instructions: You can open TPSR files using the desktop version of TeamViewer software. If installed on your compture, double-clciking the TPSR file will open it in TeamViewer software. TPSR files can be exported to PDF files as well or can be printed to have a printed copy of the protocol file.
